headline: Dell and HP Inc. Stocks Get Price-Target Boosts Ahead of Earnings. Why One of the Stocks Is a Buy.
summary: Analysts at  Citi  raised price targets for  Dell Technologies  and  HP Inc.  ahead of the companies’ earnings reports but cautioned that the enterprise hardware market could face headwinds through the rest of the year.  Citi maintained its Neutral rating on HP and lifted its price target to $29 from $25.  Dell  received a more bullish outlook.
